    "narrative": "The cornerstone of today\u2019s lineup is **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite 80.92 score against Civale. With a favorable park factor and strong SP skill metrics, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is the clear anchor of the LawDog offense. He is joined in the top tier by **Jonathan Aranda** (66.61) and **Bryson Stott** (63.33), both of whom benefit significantly from dynamic platoon advantages against Mahle and Paddack, respectively. **Taylor Ward** also provides a high-floor start at 61.36; despite the challenge of facing Fried, **Taylor Ward** maintains value through a premium leadoff spot and a positive platoon edge that offsets the quality of the opposing arm.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card was opting to start **Matt Chapman** (43.27) and **Masyn Winn** (43.78) over **Luis Arraez** (42.11). While **Luis Arraez** provides stability, his lack of category juice in SB and HR often renders him a lower-ceiling play in our 5x5 framework compared to the speed-inflected profiles of **Masyn Winn** and the power potential of **Matt Chapman**. We are keeping a close eye on **Jeremiah Jackson** (42.80); while he remains in the lineup, his exposure against Fried is mitigated by the risk of an elite holder limiting his SB opportunities. **Wenceel Perez** remains a startable asset at 48.73, though his low dynamic platoon score indicates we are riding his volume rather than a premium matchup.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the volatile environment for our fringe starters. The matchup against Fried poses the greatest risk for **Taylor Ward** and **Jeremiah Jackson**, while **Geraldo Perdomo** faces a stiff test against Boyd, though his position in the two-hole keeps his projection safely above our 40-point threshold. Note that **Cal Raleigh**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Will Smith**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** are excluded from today\u2019s active rotation; **Lawrence Butler** would have been a high-priority pivot had he been confirmed in his lineup, but he remains benched alongside **Jung Hoo Lee**, who fell below our minimum efficiency floor of 40.0.",
